<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-a27774ed-7fff-9146-6da5-3a9662f05649"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">This exam paves the way for admissions in IITs, NITs, IIITs and CFTIs. A number of architectural colleges accept the admissions on the basis of the JEE Main result and Scorecard. The exam is set to take place in April 2020 and about 12 lakh students are expected to appear for the JEE Main exam. The students who clear the JEE Main will be eligible for the <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-advanced" target="_blank">JEE Advanced</a> phase which is scheduled in April 2020. This exam helps you with the entrance in 31 NITs, 20 IIITs, and 18 CFTIs.</span></span></p>
&nbsp;

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><u style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span id="docs-internal-guid-82edb471-7fff-7dcc-ae25-07549a562506"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JEE Main Exam Pattern</span></span></u></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Please note that NTA conducts two JEE Main exams yearly now so as to save a year for the candidates. The students can appear in either or both of these exams.&nbsp;</span></span></p>
&nbsp;

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-a27774ed-7fff-9146-6da5-3a9662f05649"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JEE Main constitutes of two papers. The Paper I is meant for the B.E/B. Tech students and the Paper II is dedicated to the students appearing for the B.Arch / B.Planning courses via JEE Main. Here is a brief of the same-</span></span></p>
