<p>Now that you have an idea about the <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/exam-pattern" target="_blank">JEE Main Exam Pattern</a> and marking scheme, please note that the application forms for JEE Main 2020 are now filled. Yes, the last date of registering for the JEE Main exam was 10th October 2019. Now that it is over, the registered candidates can move to check and verify their details again so as to proceed with the application correction process.</p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><u><span id="docs-internal-guid-7e7189d9-7fff-8fea-5264-235dd66bc408"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JEE Main Eligibility Criteria</span></span></u></p>
&nbsp;

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7e7189d9-7fff-8fea-5264-235dd66bc408"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Before registering yourself for the exam, it is advised to please go through the eligibility criteria and check if you fit in to appear for the exam. Let’s have a quick look at the <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/eligibility-criteria" target="_blank">JEE Main Eligibility Criteria</a>-</span></span></p>
&nbsp;

<ul dir="ltr">
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7e7189d9-7fff-8fea-5264-235dd66bc408"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Educational Background- The candidate must be either appearing or must have cleared the 10+2 level exam or equivalent from an authorized university or board.</span></span></li>
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7e7189d9-7fff-8fea-5264-235dd66bc408"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Students who hold a diploma are also eligible. But the exception for the diploma holders will be that they will only be considered for the IITs. The scorecard will not be applicable for NITs and CFTIs.</span></span></li>
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7e7189d9-7fff-8fea-5264-235dd66bc408"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As per the minimum marks criteria, the candidates from the General category must be able to score 75% in their 12th boards or must be in the top 20 percentile in the 12th class examination. However, for the SC/ST candidates, the qualifying marks are 65% marks.</span></span></li>
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7e7189d9-7fff-8fea-5264-235dd66bc408"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The candidate must be an Aadhar Card Holder.</span></span></li>
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7e7189d9-7fff-8fea-5264-235dd66bc408"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">There is a prescribed age limit for the exam. Earlier, the age limit was 24 years.</span></span></li>
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7e7189d9-7fff-8fea-5264-235dd66bc408"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As per the specific subject criterion, the candidates must have passed Mathematics, Physics along with Chemistry, Biology, Biotechnology, or any other technical vocational subject from the 5 subjects opted.</span></span></li>
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-7e7189d9-7fff-8fea-5264-235dd66bc408"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The students who have passed their 12th board examination in the year 2019 and 2020 are eligible to apply.</span></span></li>
</ul>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.92;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:8pt;"><u><span id="docs-internal-guid-9f1f9319-7fff-3285-facc-844f84573754"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(54, 54, 54); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">IIT JEE Admit Card</span></span></u></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:2.034782608695652;margin-top:11pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-9f1f9319-7fff-3285-facc-844f84573754"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">It is mandatory to carry the admit card or call letter when appearing for the exam. The admit card can be downloaded with the combination of your Application number and Date of Birth.</span></span></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:2.034782608695652;margin-top:11pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-9f1f9319-7fff-3285-facc-844f84573754"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Steps to download the IIT JEE Admit Card-</span></span></p>

<ul dir="ltr">
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 2.03478; margin-top: 11pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-9f1f9319-7fff-3285-facc-844f84573754"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Go to the <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/admit-card" target="_blank">JEE Main 2020 Admit Card</a> link.</span></span></li>
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 2.03478; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-9f1f9319-7fff-3285-facc-844f84573754"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Fill in your application number and Date of Birth as filled during the registration process.</span></span></li>
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 2.03478; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-9f1f9319-7fff-3285-facc-844f84573754"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">If the details are entered correctly, you’ll be able to see your JEE 2020 Main Admit Card on your screen.</span></span></li>
  <li role="presentation" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 2.03478; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-9f1f9319-7fff-3285-facc-844f84573754"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Verify the details and download the same. It is suggested to take more than one printouts, to be on the safer side.</span></span></li>
</ul>

<p>The <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/admit-card" target="_blank">JEE Main Admit Card</a> for the January session will be out on 6th December 2020.&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;"><u><span id="docs-internal-guid-ef13bfa4-7fff-f426-5893-3c84cf58a76e"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JEE Main Test Series</span></span></u></p>

<p>JEE Main Test Series assist in practice and analyzing preparation level. Moreover, taking this test series will help in practicing all types of questions asked in JEE Mains 2020. Testbook is providing engineering entrance exam candidates free <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/test-series">JEE Main Test Series</a>. Under this, you will find two JEE Main full test that includes 75 questions each. Check the below features to understand about JEE Main Test Series and how it will ace your practice and preparations.</p>

<p><strong>JEE Main Test Series Features</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>Each free test includes 75 Questions for 300 marks.</li>
  <li>You have to attempt 75 questions within 180 mins.</li>
  <li>All the Questions are based on the JEE Main last year papers and syllabus.</li>
  <li>Attempting the JEE Main Test Series will give hands-on practice and familiarity with all types of questions.</li>
</ul>

<p align="center"><a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/test-series" target="_blank">Attempt JEE Main Test Series Now!</a></p>

<p><u><span id="docs-internal-guid-6e7d3e09-7fff-96f7-7025-bec96ddf23be"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JEE Mains 2020 Exam Cut Off</span></span></u></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:2.034782608695652;margin-top:11pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-6e7d3e09-7fff-96f7-7025-bec96ddf23be"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/cutoff" target="_blank">JEE Main Cutoff</a> works as a qualifying criterion for JEE Advanced. It decides the opening and closing ranks who have cleared the exam. The candidates who couldn’t match the desired cut off are not considered eligible for the next exam. NTA shall be releasing the Cutoff marks for the given exam as soon as the results are announced. These vary as per the reservation categories of the candidates.</span></span></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:2.034782608695652;margin-top:11pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><u><span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JEE Mains 2020 Result</span></span></u></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:2.034782608695652;margin-top:11pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-1791ebe6-7fff-b69f-d196-5b4a5068cb40"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The result for JEE Main decides if you are eligible for the JEE Advanced. Once the results are declared, you only have to login with your DOB and JEE Main Roll number. If the correct details are submitted, you’ll be able to see your JEE Main Score along with your AIR i.e. All India Rank. This scorecard can be downloaded from the same page. Check the detailed information about <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/result" target="_blank">JEE Main Result </a>2020 from here.</span></span></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:2.034782608695652;margin-top:11pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><u><span id="docs-internal-guid-42e7856c-7fff-4456-bdd0-ededc316b88f"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JEE Mains 2020 Answer Key</span></span></u></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:2.034782608695652;margin-top:11pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-42e7856c-7fff-4456-bdd0-ededc316b88f"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The official IIT JEE Mains Answer key is generally released within a week of the exam. You can check the answer key and predict your marks. This will help you understand where you stand in the race. Also, there is a provision to challenge the answers. If you feel very confident about any question to be incorrect or have multiple answers, you can challenge the same. </span></span><span id="docs-internal-guid-42e7856c-7fff-4456-bdd0-ededc316b88f"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Challenging a question would cost INR 1000 per question.&nbsp;</span></span></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:2.034782608695652;margin-top:11pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><u><span id="docs-internal-guid-5ef94e1f-7fff-8802-f87b-e4cbe5b352d1"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">IIT JEE Mains Application Correction</span></span></u></p>
&nbsp;

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-5ef94e1f-7fff-8802-f87b-e4cbe5b352d1"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">It is understandable that one can make possible mistakes while filling the application form. It could be due to some technical glitch or our own carelessness. NTA understands the same and gives a chance to edit the submitted application form. You can edit all the details except the examination center. Once you recheck all the details thoroughly and edit the needful, you can save the final version. Please note that this chance will be given to you only once at certain charges. So, once you are making the edits, recheck all the details thoroughly.</span></span></p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">As per the latest updates, the JEE Main Form correction process has begun and&nbsp;shall continue till 20th October 2020. Ace your JEE Main exam preparations with Testbook!<br>
<br>
&nbsp;</p>

<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><u><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">FAQs about JEE Main 2020</span></span></u></p>
&nbsp;

<p style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre; line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">1. Will this exam be conducted offline too?</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">No, JEE Mains 2020 is a Computer-based Test which only conducted online.</span></span><br>
&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2. How many times can a candidate appear for IIT JEE Mains examination?</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JEE Mains is now conducted twice a year. Whether the student chooses to appear for just one or both exams, the attempts in one academic year will be considered as one. Other than that, a student can appear for the JEE Mains for 3 consecutive years.</span></span><br>
&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">3. I filled 2 application forms for JEE Mains 2020. Will that be considered?</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">As per NTA, filling multiple forms can lead to cancellation.&nbsp; However, just one form will be considered and an admit card will be generated for the same.</span></span><br>
&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">4. Will I be able to edit my application form?</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Yes, the candidates will be able to edit the application form. The option will be available in October.</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">5. When will NTA release the JEE Main Admit Card?</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">NTA has released the JEE Main Admit Card on the 6th of December 2020. Get the direct link to check the <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/admit-card" target="_blank">JEE Main Admit Card</a> and also know the steps to download the same from the official website.</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6. When is the JEE Main 2020 scheduled?</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The JEE Main is scheduled between 6th to 9th January 2020. Know about the <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/exam-date" target="_blank">JEE Main exam date</a> from this link and stay updated about important dates.</span></span><br>
&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7. Can I take my calculator along with me?</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-d1572e67-7fff-45a8-8928-48c048edd510"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">No calculators or electronic devices are permitted in the examination center.</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">8. What all things are prohibited in the JEE Main examination centre?</span></span></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><font face="Arial" color="#000000"><span style="font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;">Candidates are only permitted to carry JEE Main Admit Card. They cannot carry Calculators, rules, pens, electronic watches, log tables, printed or written pieces of paper, pagers, mobile phones, etc. </span></font></p>

<p style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;background:white"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Candidates having 12th Certificates will only be permitted to take admission. Therefore, 11th pass candidates don't fit in the <a href="https://testbook.com/jee-main/eligibility-criteria" target="_blank">JEE Main eligibility criteria</a>.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;background:white">&nbsp;</p>
